# Quick Decisions

> For small decisions that matter but don't warrant a full Architecture Decision Record. Quick to write, easy to reference.

---

## When to Use This vs ADRs

| Use Quick Decisions | Use Full ADRs |
|---------------------|---------------|
| Personal workflow choices | Technology selection |
| Tool preferences | Architecture patterns |
| Configuration decisions | Database design |
| Style choices | Security approaches |
| Process adjustments | Breaking changes |

**Rule of thumb:** If it affects only you → here. If it affects the codebase architecture → `Decisions/` folder.

---

## Decision Log

> [!tip] **Add Your Decisions Here**
> Add new decisions directly below (newest first). Keep it brief — template is below.

---

### 2025-12-14 — Personal Section Structure
**Decision:** Create Personal/ folder with Thoughts, Prompts, Ideas, Learning, Decisions

**Why:** Need a frictionless capture system separate from project documentation. Thoughts for raw capture, Prompts for queued Claude work, Ideas for parking lot.

**Alternatives:** Single "Inbox.md" file (too messy), Tags only (hard to process systematically)

---

### 2025-12-14 — Prompt Completion Workflow
**Decision:** Mark prompts `status: completed` and archive monthly rather than delete

**Why:** Preserves history of what was requested. Can reference past prompts. Avoids accidental re-processing.

**Alternatives:** Delete after completion (loses history), Move immediately (too much file shuffling)

